  <brief_title>An Open-label Study of KW-3357</brief_title>
  <acronym>3357-004</acronym>
  <official_title>An Open-label Study of KW-3357 Compared to Plasma-derived Antithrombin for Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation (DIC) Associated With Infection</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Kyowa Hakko Kirin Co., Ltd</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Kyowa Hakko Kirin Co., Ltd</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and safety of KW-3357 compared to
      plasma-derived antithrombin using multi-center, open-label, parallel-group, comparative
      method in patients with Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation (DIC) associated with
      infection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
